##This picture of him with a bag full of pills went viral

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Xinhua News Agency client

A volunteer driver snapped this photo:

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The man with the bag full of pills
His name is Feng Feng
Huimin Yuan community grid worker, Houhu Street, Jiang'an District, Wuhan
WHO BUYS drugs for people with severe chronic diseases
February 24th, just after 5:00 a.m
Feng Feng and two colleagues
To a pharmacy on yellowstone road
Waiting in line to get a number
For failing to get a number two days in a row
That led to nearly 100 prescriptions being filled that day

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When they came out of the pharmacy,
It's almost five in the afternoon
Nearly 12 hours
They finally got it
For patients with severe illness in the community

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
But..
We can't carry all the medicine in the box
Feng Feng Feng simply took a small portion of the drug
And Strung them in two strings and hung them on me

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"because it's easy to get,
I got in the car right away."
A simple response
An ordinary figure

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That bag of pills hanging all over your body
It's the patient's hope
It's a family thing
The needs of every resident
It's all one dot
Hanging from his body
Into a complete string

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This is the grassroots community worker
A microcosm of what you do every day
Maybe not enough
Maybe not so perfect
But..
They're really trying
Salutations
All of you on the front lines!
Thank you!
